<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Lily Allen has revealed she's returned to the UK after jetting to Las Vegas to tie the knot with Stranger Things' David Harbour.</p>

<p>The singer, 35, took to Instagram Stories to reveal she's begun her two-week quarantine after marrying the actor at the Graceland Wedding Chapel last week.</p>

<p>It appears that Lily has headed back to the UK alone, as just a day earlier her new husband David was spotted out and about in New York City.</p>

<p>Home again! Lily Allen has begun her two week quarantine after returning to the UK following her Las Vegas wedding to Stranger Things' David Harbour</p>

<p>Lily posted a snap of her new office with the caption 'Quarantine Studio,' as she begun her 14 days in isolation.</p>

<p>Currently COVID-19 guidelines state that any UK resident returning from the United States must isolate for two weeks due to the country's high number of cases.  </p>

<p>After flying home it also appeared Lily had indulged in a cosy new winter coat as she posted an array of snaps of the new garment.</p>

<p>Surprise! The couple tied the knot at the Graceland Wedding Chapel in Nevada last week, mere hours after obtaining a marriage licence</p>

<p>Low-key: Lily took to Instagram Stories to share a glimpse of her makeshift office back home in Britain, with the caption: 'Quarantine studio'</p>

<p>Meanwhile Lily's new husband David was spotted out and about in NYC on Tuesday,  despite current COVID-19 regulations that require anyone returning from Nevada to New York to quarantine for 14 days.  </p>

<p>As of September 9, Nevada is listed as a restricted state on the New York government website, with the only exemption being someone who was passing through a restricted state and spent less than 24 hours there. </p>

<p>DailyMail.com contacted Harbour's representative for comment at the time.</p>

<p>New purchase? After flying home it also appeared Lily had indulged in a cosy new winter coat as she posted an array of snaps of the new garment</p>

<p>Solo: It appears that Lily has returned home solo, as her new husband David was spotted out and about in New York City on Tuesday</p>

<p>David and Lily tied the knot in Las Vegas on Monday, September 7, officiated by an Elvis Presley impersonator.</p>

<p>They divide their time between the UK and the US and sparked engagement rumours in May when Allen was seen with a sparkler on her ring finger in an Instagram post.</p>

<p>In snaps shared from the ceremony, Allen exchanged vows wearing a short 60s-inspired Dior dress with bateau neckline and veil.</p>

<p>The newlyweds celebrated their nuptials with burgers and fries from fast food chain In-N-Out.  </p>

<p>Sharing photos to his Instagram last week, Harbour wrote: 'In a wedding officiated by the king himself, the people's princess wed her devoted, low born, but kind credit card holder in a beautiful ceremony lit by the ashen skies courtesy of a burning state miles away in the midst of a global pandemic.'</p>

<p>Said 'I do': Lily and David exchanged their vows in Las Vegas on Monday, September 7, officiated by an Elvis Presley impersonator</p>
